Articles.Content:
I've been trying to get Environmental Visual Enhancements to work on my computer, but no matter what I do, it just doesn't want to cooperate. The only thing that works is the lowest resolution texture pack available. Anything higher and the game crashes a few seconds after it starts loading.

After numerous crashes, I installed Active Texture Management - Basic, only to get this:

The same thing happens with Astronomer's Visual Pack. -force-opengl doesn't work either.

System specs-

OS: Windows 7 Home Premium

Processor: AMD Athlon 64 X2 Dual Core Processor 4200+ 2.20 GHz

RAM: 4 GB (3.5 GB usable)

System Type: 32 bit

Graphics Card: ASUS EAH6450

My guess is you need to exclude the visual/planet pack from being compressed by ATM. This can be done in a CFG located in the ATM folder.

But from what I understand the benefit of ATM in 1.0.4 is slim at best. ATM works by compressing textures to the DXT format. Back in the day when most mods used PNG or TGA formats this compression saved allot of RAM, but now a days almost every self respecting mod uses DXT textures. Look in any gamedata folder and all you will find are .DDS files.

ATM causes more problems than it solves, at least for me it does.

I had this problem too. It seems that the plugin can crash while its compressing the large textures in eve and the astronomers pack. The trick is to only install a few parts of that pack at a time with no other mods then it should work. Just remember to delete the old compressed textures in the plugin dir first.

I tried installing the bare minimum and used -force-d3d11, but now it crashes just before the main menu screen. I'm considering holding off experimenting with EVE until 1.1 comes out, since KSP will be able to use more ram.

P.S. There are no other mods installed besides EVE, so memory-gobbling part packs aren't a problem.

Thanks anyway for your help so far

Some drastic tips for reducing ram:

If you care about IVA views (like I do) just delete the "Props" and "Spaces" folder in the Squad directory ( it saves about 130 MB)

Some of the stock parts are really large in size: TR-2L Wheel=5.5MB, XL3 Wheel= 2.2MB, LaunchEscapeSystem=1.5MB, Both the animated ladders=6MB, The Radiators=5MB to name a few. Just delete them and replace them with parts from mods. (IE do you realy need stock wheels when you have KF installed?).

Also keep in mind -force-d3d11 isn't a miracle drug, one my system it makes KSP run worse.

Ow and don't post logs like that, it's really hard to read in a forum box. Upload them somewhere so people can open them in programs like Notepad++
